If a function is used as the initializer of a static property declaration, should the type include `typeof`?

```ts
const returnThisMember = function ([| |]) {
    return this.member;
}

class Container {
    member = "sample";
    static returnThisMember = returnThisMember;
};
```

Right now it just becomes `this: Container`. If that's desirable, could you give me a pointer on how to get the `typeof` equivalent type from `declaration.parent`? I haven't figured it out üôÅ

